1
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:32,979
[Cage of Shadows]

2
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:36,180
[Episode 16]

3
00:01:36,759 --> 00:01:43,220
[High Art]

4
00:01:42,880 --> 00:01:44,320
You're back, Yanzhi.

5
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:44,770
Shh.

6
00:01:44,789 --> 00:01:45,550
How did it go?

7
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:47,400
Who was it?

8
00:01:47,759 --> 00:01:48,720
Was it Wan Hongliu?

9
00:01:48,720 --> 00:01:50,200
It has nothing to do with Wan Hongliu.

10
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:51,130
Not Wan Hongliu?

11
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:53,180
Then who was it?

12
00:01:56,070 --> 00:01:57,240
Anyway, rest assured.

13
00:01:57,240 --> 00:01:58,150
Tonight,

14
00:01:58,170 --> 00:01:59,900
no one will bother us anymore.

15
00:01:59,920 --> 00:02:02,030
Let's go back and get some rest,

16
00:02:02,050 --> 00:02:04,710
so we can do our best
in the final round tomorrow.

17
00:02:06,090 --> 00:02:06,730
My Lady,

18
00:02:07,370 --> 00:02:09,080
are you satisfied this time?

19
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:11,200
I often hear my father praising you.

20
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:12,710
You certainly live up to your reputation.

21
00:02:12,710 --> 00:02:14,240
Thank you for the compliment, My Lady.

22
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:15,840
I don't deserve it.

23
00:02:17,090 --> 00:02:18,850
Forgive my presumption.

24
00:02:19,160 --> 00:02:21,520
If you hate a female prisoner,

25
00:02:21,640 --> 00:02:23,600
I can take care of her for you.

26
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:25,800
Why did you come here in person?

27
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:28,079
Is it just for amusement?

28
00:02:28,100 --> 00:02:29,700
At first, I just wanted to see

29
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:31,820
what kind of person she is.

30
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,360
But I didn't expect

31
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:35,160
that at death's door,

32
00:02:35,190 --> 00:02:36,720
she would still dare to talk back to me.

33
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:37,850
That is outrageous.

34
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:41,160
Since this female prisoner
shows no remorse,

35
00:02:41,160 --> 00:02:42,360
why don't we...

36
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:42,920
No.

37
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:44,160
Let her climb.

38
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:47,220
The higher she climbs,
the harder she will fall.

39
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:48,840
You mean...

40
00:02:49,780 --> 00:02:51,880
Let her finish the last round
of the death match.

41
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:53,160
I want to see

42
00:02:53,590 --> 00:02:55,250
what she's really capable of.

43
00:03:16,990 --> 00:03:20,760
[High Art]

44
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:32,560
Hey,

45
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:33,800
wait for me!

46
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:34,880
Hurry up!

47
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:39,440
I was worried,

48
00:03:39,820 --> 00:03:40,760
so I came back.

49
00:03:45,440 --> 00:03:46,940
In this Lingya Tower,

50
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,960
those are just illusions

51
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,760
meant to numb people.

52
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:55,970
The more it is like this,

53
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:58,530
the more dangerous it becomes.

54
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:02,400
They are living human beings.

55
00:04:03,480 --> 00:04:05,080
They shouldn't be here

56
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:07,360
to be treated as playthings.

57
00:04:32,159 --> 00:04:33,360
Do you think

58
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:34,720
they would dare to shoot the arrows?

59
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:36,159
I don't think they'd dare.

60
00:04:36,159 --> 00:04:37,760
They are sisters, after all.

61
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:39,360
People who come here

62
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:40,980
are capable of anything.

63
00:04:41,010 --> 00:04:42,340
If you don't believe it,

64
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:44,159
look for yourselves.

65
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,560
They're really ruthless.

66
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:53,560
Yeah.

67
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,300
Oh.

68
00:04:55,330 --> 00:04:57,600
I'll bet on the Red Team
for today's three rounds.

69
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:59,300
I still have faith in Voice-Keeper.

70
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:00,300
Me too.

71
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:04,350
I wonder what you think
about this round, Miss?

72
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:07,650
I'll still bet
on the same one as last time.

73
00:05:23,280 --> 00:05:24,080
Not me.

74
00:05:26,080 --> 00:05:28,120
They lost points,
so we don't need to shoot.

75
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:29,270
Yeah.

76
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:42,360
So accurate.

77
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:43,280
Yeah.

78
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:51,130
For the Red Team,

79
00:05:51,350 --> 00:05:54,200
two points deducted
for spilling the shimmering elixir,

80
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:56,600
and five points added
for hitting the jade bead.

81
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:58,640
A total of three points.

82
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:00,280
Blue Team, get ready.

83
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:02,960
It seems we need to change our plan.

84
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:04,580
If we want to beat the Red Team,

85
00:06:04,580 --> 00:06:06,240
we have to shoot our arrows.

86
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:08,010
That's our only choice.

87
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:08,840
Tuya,

88
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:10,440
I'm not good at archery.

89
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:12,040
I'm afraid I'll knock it over
or hurt someone.

90
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:14,200
I'll leave the scoring to you later.

91
00:06:14,790 --> 00:06:15,590
Okay.

92
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:06,200
No, I'm not sure I can do it.

93
00:08:06,840 --> 00:08:08,300
Nan Yanzhi believes in us.

94
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:10,700
We must believe in ourselves too.

95
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:12,120
Okay.

96
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:13,960
Believe in ourselves.

97
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:42,270
Hit!

98
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,200
See?

99
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:45,640
I was right, wasn't I?

100
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:02,680
Are they really going to win?

101
00:09:02,830 --> 00:09:03,630
Impossible.

102
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:07,020
I've never seen Voice-Keeper lose
in the Hall of Elegance.

103
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:10,500
You are nothing but a convicted prisoner

104
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:12,680
who cannot even leave Lingya Tower.

105
00:09:12,690 --> 00:09:16,190
Why should I believe you can
help me find the real culprit?

106
00:09:16,410 --> 00:09:18,140
What if I can leave this Lingya Tower?

107
00:09:18,140 --> 00:09:20,680
I'm afraid you won't survive
tomorrow's death match,

108
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:22,430
let alone leave this Lingya Tower.

109
00:09:22,430 --> 00:09:23,230
Alright.

110
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:25,470
How about we make a bet?

111
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:27,380
If we meet outside in the future,

112
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:29,930
I will help you find the real culprit
who killed your husband,

113
00:09:29,930 --> 00:09:31,830
and you promise to do me a favor.

114
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:33,300
How about that?

115
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:34,840
What a pipe dream.

116
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:36,100
We can discuss this

117
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,880
after you leave Lingya Tower

118
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:39,320
and come find me.

119
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:41,640
It's a deal.

120
00:09:44,550 --> 00:09:45,360
Bow.

121
00:09:51,780 --> 00:09:53,800
I, Nan Yanzhi...

122
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:55,040
I, Jiang Man...

123
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:58,040
-...pray that Heaven blesses our dynasty
-...pray that Heaven blesses our dynasty

124
00:09:58,040 --> 00:09:59,880
-with a long reign.
-with a long reign.

125
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:01,280
-May we have an abundant harvest.
-May we have an abundant harvest.

126
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:03,000
-May the weather be favorable,
-May the weather be favorable,

127
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:06,330
-and disasters be kept at bay.
-and disasters be kept at bay.

128
00:10:12,520 --> 00:10:14,180
Offer the shimmering elixir.

129
00:10:30,980 --> 00:10:31,780
Ah!

130
00:10:33,920 --> 00:10:35,080
What happened?

131
00:10:35,100 --> 00:10:36,290
We were just one step away.

132
00:10:36,290 --> 00:10:38,090
She must have done it on purpose.

133
00:10:39,570 --> 00:10:40,690
I'm sorry.

134
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:41,520
Man.

135
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:42,680
I'm sorry.

136
00:10:45,130 --> 00:10:46,350
Did you do it on purpose?

137
00:10:46,350 --> 00:10:47,450
I know you two don't get along,

138
00:10:47,450 --> 00:10:49,080
but you shouldn't
talk about her like that.

139
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:50,560
At this point,

140
00:10:50,680 --> 00:10:52,540
she had no reason to lose her grip.

141
00:10:57,400 --> 00:10:58,440
Nan Yanzhi.

142
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,000
You lose.

143
00:11:03,760 --> 00:11:04,280
Come.

144
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:06,240
Jiang Man, get up.

145
00:11:06,780 --> 00:11:08,020
Come on, take it easy.

146
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:09,960
Oh, come on.

147
00:11:12,640 --> 00:11:14,480
If it weren't for her,

148
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:18,530
I might not have been able to beat you.

149
00:11:18,860 --> 00:11:19,820
President Wan,

150
00:11:19,850 --> 00:11:20,290
you...

151
00:11:21,220 --> 00:11:24,340
Jiang Man, I've got your back.

152
00:11:24,900 --> 00:11:26,440
There's no need to hide.

153
00:11:27,760 --> 00:11:28,640
Guards!

154
00:11:35,190 --> 00:11:36,200
Man!

155
00:11:37,160 --> 00:11:38,040
Yanzhi.

156
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:39,800
Why did you do this?

157
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:41,310
What is going on?

158
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:43,160
I was right.

159
00:11:43,890 --> 00:11:45,230
She betrayed us!

160
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:45,930
Man.

161
00:11:47,270 --> 00:11:48,760
Is what she said true?

162
00:11:50,170 --> 00:11:51,180
I'm sorry.

163
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:52,120
We've been through
life and death together,

164
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:54,720
and experienced so many
hardships to get here.

165
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:56,840
Why did you do such a thing?

166
00:11:57,080 --> 00:11:59,010
I finally considered you a friend.

167
00:11:59,160 --> 00:12:01,080
How could you do this
at a matter of life and death?

168
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,400
Why did you do it?

169
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:06,680
I'm sorry, Dao.

170
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:09,280
I let you down.

171
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:11,800
I let all of you down.

172
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:15,210
Jiang Man.

173
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:18,770
You don't need to blame yourself.

174
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:22,720
You are much more sensible

175
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:25,130
than these stubborn fools.

176
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:28,240
Don't worry. I will deliver

177
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:30,800
on what I promised you.

178
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:33,370
Wan Hongliu, you are despicable!

179
00:12:33,640 --> 00:12:34,720
Chilan Tuya.

180
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:37,200
Are you jealous of me now?

181
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:40,440
I gave all of you a chance.

182
00:12:40,830 --> 00:12:43,230
I'm afraid it's too late for regrets now.

183
00:12:43,560 --> 00:12:45,160
If you want someone to blame,

184
00:12:45,280 --> 00:12:46,560
blame yourself

185
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,590
for insisting on taking her side.

186
00:12:53,290 --> 00:12:54,090
Man,

187
00:12:54,610 --> 00:12:56,160
I don't believe what she said.

188
00:12:56,160 --> 00:12:57,940
I want to hear it from you.

189
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:04,040
Tell me!

190
00:13:04,250 --> 00:13:05,330
Yanzhi...

191
00:13:06,040 --> 00:13:06,730
Man,

192
00:13:07,270 --> 00:13:08,990
I treated you like a sister.

193
00:13:09,720 --> 00:13:12,280
Didn't we agree to leave here together?

194
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:14,890
Why on earth did you do this?

195
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:18,920
I want to live.

196
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:23,080
I don't want to die.

197
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:28,730
I've had enough of living in constant fear

198
00:13:29,640 --> 00:13:31,600
and going hungry

199
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:34,040
every single day.

200
00:13:40,950 --> 00:13:42,750
Only by following President Wan

201
00:13:44,310 --> 00:13:46,390
can I live the life I want.

202
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:49,610
This is the life I want.

203
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:51,200
This is Lingya Tower.

204
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:52,960
Get this straight.

205
00:13:52,960 --> 00:13:54,160
This is Lingya Tower.

206
00:13:54,160 --> 00:13:55,880
Do you want to stay here forever?

207
00:13:55,880 --> 00:13:57,160
Haha!

208
00:13:57,590 --> 00:13:59,500
Haha!

209
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:02,980
Haha!

210
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:05,520
Lingya Tower?

211
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:08,440
Even if we get out, so what?

212
00:14:08,460 --> 00:14:11,140
The world outside is
just a bigger Lingya Tower.

213
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:12,660
I have a lowly background.

214
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:14,240
I'm not like you.

215
00:14:16,690 --> 00:14:19,750
No matter how hard I try,
I'm destined to be trampled on.

216
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:25,640
Now,

217
00:14:29,310 --> 00:14:33,660
I just want to live
like a human before I die.

218
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:36,400
You're wrong.

219
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:40,860
Now you're truly living
like less than human.

220
00:14:44,090 --> 00:14:46,680
Enough. Take them away.

221
00:15:02,300 --> 00:15:03,350
Nan Yanzhi,

222
00:15:03,750 --> 00:15:05,480
you have no power or influence.

223
00:15:05,790 --> 00:15:07,350
You can't make any waves.

224
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:11,840
Despite your best efforts,
you fell short in the end.

225
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:17,780
Human nature is sinister.

226
00:15:18,440 --> 00:15:20,500
You've finally seen it for yourself.

227
00:15:22,590 --> 00:15:23,310
Wujiu.

228
00:15:29,340 --> 00:15:30,400
Since you're back,

229
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:32,460
why didn't you report to me first?

